---
description: React and TypeScript rules
globs:
  - "src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"
  - "playground/src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: true
---

React and TypeScript rules:
- Use strict TypeScript.
- Avoid `any`.
- Export types for public component props.
- Keep components focused and small.
- Prefer named exports.
- Avoid unnecessary global state.
- Avoid browser-only APIs without guards in package code.
- Keep React and React DOM as peer dependencies.
- Do not bundle React into the library.
- Test component behavior with React Testing Library.

For React performance patterns, see `.cursor/rules/external/tech-leads-club/react-best-practices.md`.
For Node.js security in TypeScript files, see `.cursor/rules/external/security/secure-dev-node.mdc`.
